name: CMSimpleQueue
desc: An object that provides a simple lockless queue of elements.

items.name: func enqueue(UnsafeRawPointer)
items.desc: Enqueues an element in the queue.

items.name: func dequeue() -> UnsafeRawPointer?
items.desc: Dequeues an element from the queue.

items.name: var head: UnsafeRawPointer?
items.desc: The head element in the queue.

items.name: var capacity: Int
items.desc: The number of elements that a queue can hold.

items.name: var count: Int
items.desc: The number of elements currently in the queue.

items.name: var fullness: Float
items.desc: The fullness of a queue as a percentage of its capacity.

items.name: static var typeID: CFTypeID
items.desc: The type identifier of sample buffer objects.

items.name: struct CMSimpleQueue.Error
items.desc: A structure that defines errors that queue operations can produce.
